<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-610-345  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 610 345.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  Nov 8 1990 v16 n23 p70(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Plesman Publications Ltd. (Canada) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Comdisco, IST to offer joint recovery services. (Comdisco DisasterRecovery Services Inc. and Industrielle-Services Techniques Inc.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Comdisco Disaster Recovery Services Inc. (Services)Industrielle-Services Techniques Inc. (Services).andO;Topic:     Disaster RecoveryConsultantsBusiness Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Comdisco, IST to offer joint recovery servicesandM;ROSEMONT, Ill.andP;  -- Comdisco Disaster Recovery Services Inc. (CDRS) hasestablished a strategic partnership with Industrielle-Services TechniquesInc. (IST) to jointly develop, deliver and market consulting servicesthroughout Quebec, the Maritimes and the National Capital Region in Ottawa.andM;IST is a computer services firm with corporate recovery consulting servicesheadquartered in Montreal.andP;  The partnership is an extension of a marketingagreement signed in July, 1989, which made IST the marketing agent for thehot- and cold-site recovery service of CDRS while providing hot-siteextension facilities in Montreal.andM;Outsourcing servicesandM;Established in 1974, IST provides computer-based outsourcing services inQuebec.andP;  It is also a leading provider of integrated solutions for Canadianhealthcare institutions.andP;  For many years, IST had a dedicated team ofconsulting specialists involved in all phases of the evaluation and theimplementation of recovery planning services with government organizationsand private enterprises.andM;The sharing of this experience with the consulting area of CDRS, ComdiscoConsulting Services, will enhance the depth of knowledge and experience thatboth organizations can bring to their clients.andM;Edward Evans, president of Comdisco Consulting Services, stated: &quot;Using theCDRS methodolgy, this staff of experienced consultants will use industryexpertise in dealing with the recovery planning solutions to the Canadianbusiness and governmental community.&quot;andM;IST employs eight full-time corporate disaster recovery planning consultantsat its headquarters in Montreal and in its Ottawa and Quebec consultingoffices.andP;  As part of the agreement, IST will have access to CDRS's planningmethodology and will also function as a distributor of CDRS's PC-basedplanning software, ComPAS 2E.andM;Founded in 1980, CDRS provides computer disaster recovery services with over2,100 subscribers worldwide.andP;  It provides a network of fully-equippedcomputer and business recovery facilities which are available in the event offire, flood, power outage or any other disaster affecting a customer's datacentre or end-user area.andO;</TEXT></DOC>